# By Sandrine Couture - AI Development Rules

## 🎨 Design System
- Use the established "Liquid Glass" aesthetic: blurred backgrounds, subtle borders (`border-black/5`), and high-end typography.
- Colors: Primary (Pink/Magenta accents), Secondary (Soft pinks/whites), Accent (Dark/Black for text and grounding).
- Animations: Use `animate-in`, `fade-in`, `slide-in-from-bottom` for all entry sections.

## 📁 Architecture
- **Server Components:** Default to server components in `/app`. Use `"use client"` only for interactivity.
- **Component Placement:**
  - `/components/layout`: Global structure (Navbar, Footer, Schema, AI).
  - `/components/pages`: Main page wrappers.
  - `/components/home`: Sections specific to the landing page.
  - `/components/ui`: Atomic, reusable UI elements.

## 🔍 SEO & Metadata
- Always use the metadata template from `app/layout.tsx`.
- Each new page must have its own `layout.tsx` (or metadata export) and `SchemaOrgBreadcrumb`.
- Use descriptive `alt` tags for all images in `/public/images/realisations`.

## 🛠 Coding Standards
- Use TypeScript for all new files.
- Prefer absolute imports with `@/`.
- Keep components focused and reusable.
- Follow the "Agentic Coding" flow: Plan in `docs/design.md` before implementing.
